Is there a nicer way to do these steps? `rw [G.card_edgeFinset_sup_edge na ne, Nat.lt.base]` doesn't work because the inner instances corresponding to the `Sup` don't match.

I fixed it (by generalising the fintype assumptions appearing on the LHS of earlier lemmas) and then found a golf which made the fix redundant. Here's the fixed ungolfed version for your instruction:
```
theorem not_cliqueFree_of_isTuranMaximal (hn : r â‰¤ Fintype.card V) (hG : IsTuranMaximal G r) :
    Â¬G.CliqueFree r := by
  by_contra cf
  obtain âŸ¨K, _, rflâŸ© := exists_smaller_set (univ : Finset V) r hn
  have := (G.isNClique_iff).not.mp (cf K)
  simp_rw [and_true, IsClique, Set.Pairwise, not_forall] at this
  obtain âŸ¨a, _, b, _, ne, naâŸ© := this
  refine not_not_intro hG ?_
  simp_rw [IsTuranMaximal, hG.1, true_and]; push_neg
  use G âŠ” edge a b, inferInstance, cf.sup_edge a b
  rw [card_edgeFinset_sup_edge]
  exacts [lt_add_one _, na, ne]
```

```suggestion
* `SimpleGraph.IsTuranMaximal`: `G.IsTuranMaximal r` means that `G` has the most number of edges for
  its number of vertices while still being `r + 1`-cliquefree.
* `SimpleGraph.turanGraph n r`: The canonical `r + 1`-cliquefree TurÃ¡n graph on `n` vertices.
```

You're missing a theorem of the form
```

```
You might as well use it to replace `turanGraph_eq_top_of_le`

I think the `_of_le` part is not very informative

```

@[simp]

  simp_rw [SimpleGraph.ext_iff, Function.funext_iff, turanGraph, top_adj, eq_iff_iff, not_iff_not]
  refine âŸ¨fun h â†¦ ?_, ?_âŸ©
  Â· contrapose! h
    use âŸ¨0, (Nat.pos_of_ne_zero h.1).trans h.2âŸ©, âŸ¨r, h.2âŸ©
    simp [h.1.symm]
  Â· rintro (rfl | h) a b

```
